definition: to change/to become different/to transform/to vary/rebellion
(of sth) to move/to set in movement/to displace/to touch/to make use of/to stir (emotions)/to alter/abbr. for 動詞|动词[dong4 ci2], verb

sentences.english: I further represent that I will notify GMI of any material changes in writing.
sentences.chinese: 此外，我保證將以書面形式通知GMI任何變動情況。

sentences.english: The reality is that the market has changed and I need to change to the new realities.
sentences.chinese: 可目前的現實是市場發生了變動而我必須因時應事。

sentences.english: The global fast dynamics for the generalized symmetric regularized long wave equation is considered.
sentences.chinese: 考慮了對稱正則長波方程的整體快變動力學。

sentences.english: If the rate of change of neutrons is zero, so be it.
sentences.chinese: 如果中子的變動率是0，那就是它了。

sentences.english: Amount of off-replenish is high, maybe a chemistry change would be more appropriate.
sentences.chinese: 數量重新補充大，可能化學變動是更加適當的。

sentences.english: The other big corporate tax change now occurring will be negative for capital spending.
sentences.chinese: 目前另一項公司稅收大變動不利於資本支出。

sentences.english: This paper studied the cycle-to-cycle variation of in-cylinder peak pressure in gasoline engines.
sentences.chinese: 本文對汽油機最高爆發壓力的循環變動進行了研究。

sentences.english: The subsurface fluid and fluid force produced by subsurface fluid universally exist and have influence on tectonism.
sentences.chinese: 地下流體及流體力普遍存在且對構造變動產生影響。

sentences.english: Any major non leagued teams removed or added?
sentences.chinese: 那關於其他非聯賽球隊的變動情況呢？

sentences.english: Who help you manage the change of car info?
sentences.chinese: 當汽車信息變動時，誰幫你修改它。

sentences.english: This is like building a building with a measuring rod that constantly changes.
sentences.chinese: 這就好比建造一棟建築，而測量桿卻不停的在變動。

sentences.english: What should people living in permafrost areas be doing to adapt to these changes?
sentences.chinese: 住在永凍土區域的人們應該做着什麼適應這些變動？

sentences.english: And what will happen to asset prices if the boomers try to cash in their portfolios?
sentences.chinese: 如果他們決定取現，那麼資產的價格會發生何種變動？

sentences.english: This research is to study the influential factors of the housing sold prices.
sentences.chinese: 本研究系探討影響中古屋成交價格的變動因素。

sentences.english: He expects Yahoo to be compensated for the move.
sentences.chinese: 他期望雅虎公司能夠因該變動得到補償。

sentences.english: There are probably a variety of reasons for the drastic changes in peoples moral concepts.
sentences.chinese: 人們道德觀替考劇烈變動可能有不一樣替考端由。

definition: to undulate/to fluctuate/wave motion/rise and fall
to agree (to do sth)/should/ought to/must/(legal) shall
to answer/to respond/to comply with/to deal or cope with
whole entity/entire body/synthesis/as a whole (situation, construction, team etc)/global/macrocosm/integral/holistic/whole
to delay/to postpone/to keep putting sth off/to procrastinate/(computing) to lag
